The food was good.  If I was rating just the food I would give it like 4 stars (Tribos Peri Peri in NJ is way better).  However, the cashier was so rude to me as soon as I approached her to order take out that I have to give this place 2 stars.  It's weird, you would think I did something for her to behave the way she did but nope, I just walked up and that was it.  Maybe she was having a bad day, no idea, but it took a lot for me not to walk out.  The only reason I stayed is because I'm on a work trip, I have been to the Nando's in London, and I wanted my coworkers to try their food while we had the chance since they're not everywhere in the US.  Next time I'm in town I'll just try another location.  It's not worth dealing with the attitude.  UPDATE (8/29/19): Been awhile since I posted this review but I would like to give an update.  So a few days after I posted a representative got in touch with me, apologized for the issue, and offered to send me a coupon so that I could give it another try.  They said they would mail it to me and asked for my info.  Anyway, like 3 weeks later I contacted them and they said it would arrive in a day or two.  It's been months now, MONTHS, and nothing ever arrived.  I feel like they just told me that in order to see if that would change my review but nope, instead of the 2 stars I originally gave them now they get 1 instead for just being terrible not only at the store but also at the customer service level.  UPDATE (2/6/20): Please disregard the thoughtless reply by Nando's asking me to contact them. If they had actual humans replying to these things, they would've noticed what I wrote about their failure at customer service. This just makes it worse.

I am a first year med student at UM and the Nando’s on Baltimore Street has been giving me life and helping preserve my sanity lately. I used to go to the one on Fleet Street when I was at Hopkins which is nice, I had no idea this other Nando’s exited in the city. All I want to say is the food is always amazing and the team is always so polite efficient. There is a team member there that always radiates sunshine and I’ve heard her being called V. V is doing the Lord’s work with her positivity. I would tell her in person but I’m afraid my blushing would give me away. Great food and service. I look forward to my weekly visits so much. Why is Nando’s so good? Went to Nando’s on Baltimore Street yesterday afternoon and I’m just going need to know who that manager was. This Nando’s passed the vibe check. I dined in with a friend and there was a lady that came in without a mask and I could tell one of the team members went to grab the manager. She came from the back area and had such a presence. It made me feel safe. She is also very good looking, like almost too handsome. Either way, the food was good and the vibe was good. This place passes the vibe check. Also, I think the young man at the counter was Kevin? And the manager was light skinned, and beautiful. We will come back for the food and stay for the view.

First let me say that I love Nando’s. I have been to several locations around the world. I recently visited the location on West Baltimore St in Baltimore, MD. I work in DC so I usually visit your locations there but had to come to Baltimore for business. I of course expect great customer service at Nando’s but this was above and beyond. Didn’t get the name of the manager but she was y’all with shirt dark hair. This location was very busy at the time and the way she commanded the shift with grace and style made me want to offer her a job in politics. If she ran for office, I would vote for her in a heart beat. And she did this all with a smile. I could tell the team really responds to her leadership. I will be stuck in DC for the next few weeks, may you share her contact info? Who knew Nando’s could recruit such rare and poised talent! I will be back to this location whenever I come to Baltimore!

The chicken was delicious it looked like it was marinated and then fire grilled and the coleslaw was so fresh, full of beautiful colors in a light sauce. I have been to Nando's in the DC area and what a difference!  First off, me say in general - I love Nando's - however, this location in Baltimore was the worse and actually only bad experience I have ever had at a Nando's.  I always order the same thing when go - 1/2 chicken (hot) fries and salad.  The chicken was obviously left over from lunch (it was 7:00 pm when I went).  Not fresh.  My side of French fries - I  got about 10 fries (talk about portion control) and as for the salad - mostly iceberg lettuce which is not typical in DC area establishments - no tomatoes, and 1 slice of cucumber.  Needless to say, I will never go to this location again. I will drive to DC , Silver Spring, or Laurel next time, and it will be worth the trip.

This is actually the second year in a row me and my friends had gone to this particular Nando's when we convene in Baltimore. Initially, we went because of the "cheeky Nando's" meme, though we found ourselves thoroughly enjoying both the food and the drinks there. The chicken is well cooked, not greasy at all, and the sauces are both deliciously different (as compared to most chicken sauces available commonly in the US), and spicy to taste. Furthermore, while a bit on the pricey side, the sangria pitchers we had hit the spot with their seasonal peach flavor!  I have gone before, and I would go again!  PS- An interesting company policy we ran into: they will not serve you alcohol if you have a vertical license, regardless of whether or not the person is legitimately over 21 with the license being unexpired. So, if you find yourself with such an ID card, do yourself a favor and bring a passport too!
